.TH RC 1 "2026-02-19" "rc" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rc \- validate exit codes and log task completion
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rc
.RI [ options ] " EXPECTED" " [KILL]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rc
compares an expected exit code to an actual exit code and logs task completion.
.PP
If the values match,
.B rc
logs a SUCCESS message.
If they differ,
.B rc
logs an ERROR message.
.PP
When
.B KILL
is supplied and values differ,
.B rc
exits with the actual exit code.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -a , " --actual " INT
Actual exit code to validate.
Defaults to
.B RC_EXIT_CODE
if set, otherwise 0.
.TP
.BR -t , " --task " TEXT
Task label used in log output.
Defaults to
.B TASK
if set.
.TP
.BR -h , " --help"
Show help and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B TASK
Default task label.
.TP
.B RC_EXIT_CODE
Default actual exit code.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.B rc --actual 0 0
.PP
.B RC_EXIT_CODE=1 TASK="Deploy" rc 0
.PP
.B RC_EXIT_CODE=2 TASK="Deploy" rc 0 KILL
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success or mismatch without KILL.
.TP
.B 2
Invalid usage or invalid numeric values.
.PP
When mismatch occurs with
.B KILL,
.B rc
returns the actual exit code.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR et (1),
.BR loggerx (1)
